Class Animal

java.lang.Object
animals.Animal

    • distToSquared

      public double distToSquared(World world, Location from, Location to)

      Parameters:
      world - World that from and to are in
      from - Location one for the calculation
      to - Location two for the calculation
      Returns:
      The squared distance between from and to.

    • reproduce

      protected Set<Animal> reproduce(Class<?> c, World world)
      Reproduces with the closest animal of the same class, given that they are within adjacent tiles. Reproduces non-stop if the implementation does not have an energy requirement.
      Parameters:
      c - The class of the animal to breed with and the baby to be born.
      world - The world in which it reproduces.
      Returns:
      Set of Animals that this reproduce call created.

    • eat

      public void eat(World world, Edible edible)
      Eats supplied edible object by calling getEaten(World) on that object. Removes returned value from hunger and adds it to energy.
      Parameters:
      world - World that the edible object is in
      edible - The object to eat

    • eat

      public void eat(World world, Location tile)
      If the tile in world contains an object that is an instance of one of the edible classes from the getEdibleClasses()-method, then it is eaten with eat(World, Edible)-method.
      Parameters:
      world - world tile is in
      tile - tile to eat from

    • seek

      protected void seek(Class<?> c, World world, Location start, int view_distance)
      Makes use of closest_object to find an object of type c, then uses the path-method to find a path from start to that object. It then moves to the first Location in the List path returned.
      Parameters:
      c - Type to seek
      world - World to seek in
      start - Where to seek from
      view_distance - How far away the target can be
